\subsection{Free energy and phase transition}

For the U-shaped solution (\ref{finTUsol}), the function ${\cal F}$ defined
in (\ref{SandF}) is given by
\begin{eqnarray}
 {\cal F}=\int_{u_*}^\infty du\,
\frac{u}{R}\left(
\frac{1}{\sqrt{1-\frac{u_*^2(u_*^4-u_T^4)}{u^2(u^4-u_T^4)}}}-1
\right)-\frac{u_*^2}{2R}\ .
\end{eqnarray}

For the disconnected solution $y={\rm constant}$, we get
\begin{eqnarray}
 {\cal F}=-\frac{u_T^2}{2R}\ ,
\end{eqnarray}
which is independent of $u_*$.

For $u_*\gg u_T$ (small $L$), we have
\begin{eqnarray}
 L\simeq 2f_0\frac{R^2}{u_*}\ ,
~~~{\cal F}\simeq -f_0\frac{u_*^2}{R}\ ,
\end{eqnarray}
and
\begin{eqnarray}
{\cal F}\simeq -4 f_0^3\frac{R^3}{L^2}\ ,
\end{eqnarray}
which are the same as (\ref{expFL})
and (\ref{FL}). This is expected
because the asymptotic behavior in the region $u\gg u_T$
is not affected by the temperature.

Another configuration with small $L$ is obtained when
$u_*$ approaches $u_T$. In the limit $u_*\rightarrow u_T$, we have
\begin{eqnarray}
 L&\simeq&-\frac{R^2}{4u_T}
\sqrt{\epsilon_*}\log\epsilon_*\ ,
\\
{\cal F}&\simeq&-\frac{u_T^2}{2R}\left(
1+\frac{\epsilon_*}{4}\log\epsilon_*\right)\ ,
\end{eqnarray}
where $\epsilon_*\equiv (u_*/u_T)^4-1$.

